Package common

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IntSet
    Interface for an ordered set of integers that allows efficient (1) iteration (normal and reversed order) and (2) efficient tests of set membership.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IntSet.IntSetFromBitSet
    Wrapper class for obtaining an IntSet from a BitSet.
    IntSet.SingletonIntSet
    Convenience class for simulating a singleton set
    IterableBitSet
    Convenience class to loop easily over the set/clear bits of a BitSet.
    IterableStateSet
    A convenience wrapper around IterableBitSet that handles the three cases of iterating over the set or cleared bits of a BitSet representing a set of states as well as iterating over all states if the BitSet is null.
    IteratorTools
    Convenience methods for performing operations on Iterators / Iterables
    PeriodicTimer
    This class keeps time, returning true for the method triggered() when another period of period milliseconds has elapsed.
    SafeCast
    This class provides utility methods to allow the detection of primitive cast errors, e.g.
    StackTraceHelper
    Helper class for converting stack traces to strings for output
    StopWatch
    Stop watch for keeping track of the runtime of some computation, optionally printing the elapsed time to the log after the computation has stopped.
    Timeout
    Simple timeout mechanism.
